African horse sickness, Mozambique
----------------------------------
Information received on 8 May 2014 from Dr Jose Libombo Jr, National Director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Maputo, Mozambique

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 20 Mar 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 24 Apr 2014
Report date: 7 May 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 8 May 2014
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Orbivirus
Serotype: not typed
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1 (01 / MZ / 2014): Equestrian Center of Maputo, Urbano Kamubukwane, Urbano Kamubukwane, Maputo
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 Mar 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 150 / 2 / 2 / 0 / 0
Affected population: adult animals with respiratory difficulties

Outbreak 2 (01 / MZ / 2014): Costa do Sol, Kampfumo, Kampfumo, Maputo
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 Mar 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 50 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: adult male that died

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 200 / 3 / 3 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics rates apparent, expressed in percentages):
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 1.50 / 1.50 / 100 / 1.50
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and / or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; screening; vaccination in response to the outbreak (s); dipping / spraying; no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute (OVI), South Africa (OIE's reference laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Equidae / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 24 Apr 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

